arChildNodes.szComment: A anguished victim of a Blackweald pyre speaks with Torben/player, attempting to describe who did this to him. He recalls a mercenary woman (Stana) and being taken into the depths of the Scar; tortured.
The anguished pyre victim utters his last words, recalling being forced to watch other victims die by fire.
Torben speaks to now being sure that Stana, his old leader, is orchestrating this suffering/death. He is disgusted by the thought that she survived Brione's burning.
Torben speaks to Stana finding great pleasure in the suffering of others; especially by fire. He recalls the horrifying joy he saw in her eyes long ago.
Torben speaks to the pressing action to kill Stana now before she can sow more death. If she so wishes to see him (the Bear) again, she will--with all of his anger/strength aimed at her.
Torben tells the player to meet him near the depths of the Scar. They'll face Stana (within) together.
